###Answer:
*In order to update a protected range, you need to make a `batchUpdate` request and specify the `namedRangeId` and `protectedRangeId`.*
###Using the Sheets API:

Build your request:

```lang-py
request = {
            &quot;requests&quot;: [
              {
                &quot;updateNamedRange&quot;: {
                  &quot;namedRange&quot;: {
                    &quot;name&quot; : &quot;New name&quot;, #optional, only if you want to change the name
                    &quot;namedRangeId&quot;: &quot;&lt;named-range-id&gt;&quot;,
                    &quot;range&quot;: {
                      &quot;sheetId&quot;: &quot;&lt;sheet-id&gt;&quot;,
                      &quot;startRowIndex&quot;: int,
                      &quot;endRowIndex&quot;: int,
                      &quot;startColumnIndex&quot;: int,
                      &quot;endColumnIndex&quot;: int,
                    },
                  },
                 &quot;fields&quot;: &quot;*&quot;
                }
              },
              {
                &quot;updateProtectedRange&quot;: {
                  &quot;protectedRange&quot;: {
                    &quot;protectedRangeId&quot;: &lt;protected-range-id&gt;,
                    &quot;namedRangeId&quot;: &quot;&lt;named-range-id&gt;&quot;,
                    &quot;warningOnly&quot;: False,
                    &quot;editors&quot;: {
                      &quot;users&quot;: [
                        &quot;user1@email.com&quot;,
                        &quot;user2@email.com&quot;,
                      ],
                    }
                  },
                  &quot;fields&quot;: &quot;*&quot;
                }
              }
            ]
          }
```
Then send your request using the discovery library:
```lang-py
from googleapiclient import discovery

def main():
    # authentication code goes here
    service = discovery.build(&#39;sheets&#39;, &#39;v4&#39;, credentials = &lt;your-#credentials&gt;)

    spreadsheetID = &#39;&lt;your-spreadsheet-ID&gt;&#39;
    request = {dictionary-object-built-above}

    req = service.spreadsheet().batchUpdate(spreadsheetId = spreadsheetID, body = request)
    response = req.execute()    
```
###Or by using the gspread library:
Once you have enabled the API and obtained a service account key [as per the gspread documentation](https://gspread.readthedocs.io/en/latest/oauth2.html), you can build your request like above but **you need to make sure that you add the service account email to the users that can edit the protected range**:
```
request = {
            &quot;requests&quot;: [
              {
                &quot;updateNamedRange&quot;: {
                  &quot;namedRange&quot;: {
                    &quot;name&quot; : &quot;New name&quot;, #optional, only if you want to change the name
                    &quot;namedRangeId&quot;: &quot;&lt;named-range-id&gt;&quot;,
                    &quot;range&quot;: {
                      &quot;sheetId&quot;: &quot;&lt;sheet-id&gt;&quot;,
                      &quot;startRowIndex&quot;: int,
                      &quot;endRowIndex&quot;: int,
                      &quot;startColumnIndex&quot;: int,
                      &quot;endColumnIndex&quot;: int,
                    },
                  },
                 &quot;fields&quot;: &quot;*&quot;
                }
              },
              {
                &quot;updateProtectedRange&quot;: {
                  &quot;protectedRange&quot;: {
                    &quot;protectedRangeId&quot;: &lt;protected-range-id&gt;,
                    &quot;namedRangeId&quot;: &quot;&lt;named-range-id&gt;&quot;,
                    &quot;warningOnly&quot;: False,
                    &quot;editors&quot;: {
                      &quot;users&quot;: [
                        &quot;user1@email.com&quot;,
                        &quot;serviceacc@projectname-XXXXXXXXXXXXX.iam.gserviceaccount.com&quot;,
                      ],
                    }
                  },
                  &quot;fields&quot;: &quot;*&quot;
                }
              }
            ]
          }
```
and then make the request with gspread:
```lang-py
import gspread
from oauth2client.service_account import ServiceAccountCredentials

def main():
    scope = [&#39;https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets&#39;]
    credentials = ServiceAccountCredentials.from_json_keyfile_name(&#39;credentials.json&#39;, scope)

    gc = gspread.authorize(credentials)
    response = gc.open_by_key(&#39;&lt;spreadsheet-id&gt;&#39;).batch_update(request)

    print(response)
```
###References:
 - [Google Sheets API v4 Reference Documentation](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api)
  - [REST Resource: spreadsheets.values](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api/reference/rest/v4/spreadsheets.values)
  - [`spreadsheets.values.batchUpdate` method](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api/reference/rest/v4/spreadsheets.values/batchUpdate)
